  "description": "Liver is one of those ingredients that divides opinions: some avoid it entirely, while others embrace it as a secret culinary delight. Growing up more than 10000 kilometers apart, we both grew up eating beef liver cooked by our grandmas in various traditional dishes. \n\nThese liver tacos are budget-friendly, quick to prepare (especially if you already have salsa on hand), require just a few ingredients, and result in tender, flavorful meat paired with your favorite salsa (we recommend [salsa roja tatemada](/recipes/charred-red-sauce/)).",
