  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Slice the liver into 1/4 cm slices.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables:<br>\n**Onions:** peel, halve, and thinly slice. **Jalapeños:** slice, remove the roots and seeds, and thinly slice.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Heat a medium-sized skillet with olive oil on medium heat. Sauté onions and chiles with a bit of salt until translucent.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Increase the heat to medium-hight, add the liver, and more salt to the onions, and cook until no pink spots are left on the liver, for about 20 minutes, stirring regularly.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover the skillet, and cook covered for about 20 minutes more, until the liver is soft.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add more salt if necessary.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Warm up the tortillas: heat a non-sticking or cast iron skillet on medium-high until hot (don’t add oil). Warm the tortillas one by one: for about 30 seconds on one side, then for about one minute on the other side, then flip again and cook a bit more, until crispy but still slightly flexible (they shouldn’t be too soft because the meat is juicy, and they may break).",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Serve all the ingredients separately: meat, tortillas, avocado, and salsa so everyone can assemble a taco with the right amount of each ingredient.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
